data.description: 🎄✨ Parranda con RUEP ✨🎄 Experience the joy of a traditional Puerto Rican holiday celebration! A parranda is a festive gathering filled with music, singing, and community, where friends and family bring festive cheer from house to house. Join us as we bring this cherished tradition to life with music, delicious food, and plenty of holiday spirit. 📅 Wednesday, December 11🕕 6:00 PM - 9:00 PM📍 Center for Latino Arts and Culture (CLAC) Celebrate the season with RUEP—don’t miss this night of fun and tradition! 🎶🎁✨

data.description: AUG is holding its annual Genetics Faculty Meet and Greet on Friday, January 24th, 2025 at 4:00 PM(exact time is subject to change) in the Life Sciences Building Atrium on Busch!  Students will rotate through tables of faculty grouped by research topic. Many of the faculty may be looking for undergrads to join their labs in the fall semester, so this is a good chance to learn about labs in the Genetics Department and meet professors and other students!    This event is open to all majors, so even if you aren't planning to major in Genetics, you can still attend! We will also provide refreshments.    Please fill out this form using your netID email to RSVP: https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSdtxLP-Zv709PmZuUetu2h_e233feq2OgUzkt558K3yTjCmjA/viewform
